{
  "texts": [
    "These additional families allowed us to capture gene families that might be absent in reference sequences but are conserved in predicted plasmids.",
    "Note that the classification of genes as backbone or cargo depends on which plasmid system is being considered.",
    "It is possible for a gene to be classified as a backbone gene with respect to one plasmid system and, at the same time, as a cargo gene with respect to another system.",
    "This is because a plasmid can be a backbone plasmid of a system and also a compound plasmid of a different system.",
    "For every non-redundant compound plasmid in the system, we calculated the fraction of genes in the plasmid that were cargo genes."
  ]
}